main event: Two unidentified objects were observed over Long Beach, Mississippi for 25-30 minutes on 1-15-65.
interesting points: The objects were observed at an altitude of approximately 1000 feet and about 1 mile east of the observer.
The objects were initially classified as 'aircraft (HELICORS-2)'.
The sighting was reported to Project Blue Book, and a memo report was generated on 28 May 1965.
The report indicates the sighting did not involve a 'Flying Saucer' or other type of Unidentified Flying Object, and did not require further investigation.
The Keesler Air Force Base, which houses training for pilots and navigators, was mentioned in relation to the case.
